# ONL531 Export Error: Account Has Been Deleted in QuickBooks Online

If you see the error:

**“ONL531 Export Error: Account has been deleted. The category or export account may be deleted or inactive in the QuickBooks Online Chart of Accounts.”**

this means one or more mapped fields on the report are no longer active in QuickBooks Online.

Until the deleted or inactive mapping is corrected, QuickBooks will block the export.

---

## Why ONL531 Happens

ONL531 occurs when one of the following has been deleted or set to inactive in QuickBooks Online:

- **Account** (category or export account)  
- **Customer** (tag)  
- **Item** (category)  
- **Vendor** (report submitter or Credit Card Misc. vendor)  
- **Class**  

If any of these mapped values no longer exist or are inactive in QuickBooks, the export fails.

This is a QuickBooks Online mapping issue — not a connection failure.

---

## Who Can Fix ONL531

You must be a **Workspace Admin** in Expensify and have access to manage accounts or settings in QuickBooks Online.

---

## How to Refresh the Export Configuration in Expensify

To reset and refresh the export mapping:

1. Go to the navigation tabs on the left.
2. Click **Settings**.
3. Click **Workspaces**.
4. Select your Workspace.
5. Click **Accounting**.
6. Click **Configure**.
7. Open the **Export** tab.
8. Under **Export Reimbursable/Non-reimbursable Expenses As**, select a different export option.
9. Click **Save**.
10. Click **Configure** again.
11. Re-select the correct export type.
12. Click **Save**.

This refreshes the mapping between Expensify and QuickBooks Online.

---

## How to Retry Exporting After ONL531

After refreshing the export configuration:

1. Open the affected report.
2. Retry exporting the report.
3. Confirm the export completes successfully.

If the error continues, confirm that all mapped values (accounts, vendors, customers, items, classes) are active in QuickBooks Online.

---

# FAQ

## Does ONL531 mean my QuickBooks connection is broken?

No. It means one of the mapped values used in the export has been deleted or set to inactive in QuickBooks Online.

---

## Can members fix this error?

Members can update categories or tags on their reports, but a Workspace Admin must refresh the export configuration and confirm QuickBooks mappings.

---

## Do I need to reconnect QuickBooks Online?

No. Refreshing the export configuration and retrying the export is typically sufficient.
